        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>747</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-0032</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-0032.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Bessel's inequality">Bessel's inequality</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U = \{u_n : n \in  \mathbb {N}\}]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0029.xml" addr="FA-0029" title="Orthonormal sequence">orthonormal sequence</fr:link> in a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0030.xml" addr="FA-0030" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  H]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>Then,</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(a)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sum _{n \in  \mathbb {N}} |\langle  u_n, x \rangle |^2 \leq  ||x||^2]]></fr:tex>;</fr:p>
            <fr:p>(can be seen as an <fr:em>infinite-dimensional Pythagorean theorem</fr:em>)</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(b)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_U \stackrel {\text {def}}{=} \sum _{n=1}^{+\infty } \langle  u_n, x \rangle  u_n]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0026.xml" addr="FA-0026" title="Convergent">convergent</fr:link> sum;</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>(c)</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x - x_U \in  U^\perp ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>(of course <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U^\perp ]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0031.xml" addr="FA-0031" title="Orthogonal complement">orthogonal complement</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>)</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>749</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-0041</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-0041.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Direct sum">Direct sum</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The direct sum of two vector subspaces <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> of a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \oplus  V]]></fr:tex>, is the set of all vectors that can be uniquely expressed as the sum of a vector from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> and a vector from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Formally, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \oplus  V = \{u + v : u \in  U, v \in  V\}]]></fr:tex> where the representation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w = u + v]]></fr:tex> is unique for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w \in  U \oplus  V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>For the direct sum to exist, the subspaces must satisfy the condition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \cap  V = \{0\}]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{0\}]]></fr:tex> is the zero vector. This ensures the uniqueness of the representation.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In the context of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0030.xml" addr="FA-0030" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is a closed subspace, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H = M \oplus  M^\perp ]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^\perp ]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0031.xml" addr="FA-0031" title="Orthogonal complement">orthogonal complement</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>. This means every vector <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  H]]></fr:tex> can be uniquely written as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = m + n]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \in  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \in  M^\perp ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
